            <sv:value>&lt;p&gt;[TBD]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In our contacts example, we want to have 10+ contacts, simply just first name, last name, organization, maybe photo. We want to have one page lists all of them, or maybe have them already listed and dropdown in navigation, and of coruse these lists will link to each contact detail page. But we don&amp;#39;t want our editors completely create all these subpages forcing them to follow some desfin/layout paterns, same for creating this list manualy link by link.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instread of that we may have custom Content App for our contacts - new workspace with set of dialogs and tools (maybe with special editors permissions) just to manage this contacts. And do not care about how they will be displayed on pages. Because thats your front-end guy work. Lets have a look how to create and configure automaticaly genereated link lists, navigation dropdowns and dynamic detail pages for our contatcs and how you can reuse it for any indexed data your project need.&lt;/p&gt;
